					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546" rend="visible">
						<summary>A commentary on Tiḳune Zohar.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Aramaic of the Zohar</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546">
							<locus from="1r" to="242v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Or yaḳar (Tiḳune Zohar)</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">אור יקר (תקוני הזהר)</title>
							<note>
								<p>The volume is uniform with Add MS 27060 and begins where the other broke off, containing gates 6-10 of Bava ḳama.</p>
								<p>Notes on the subjects treated in the volume are found on folio 2r.</p>
							</note>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/12317536">Cordovero, Moses ben Jacob, 1522-1570</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/12317536">קורדוברו, משה, 1522-1570</persName>
							</author>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">שלם ע"י הצעיר <name type="person" role="scribe">יעק[ב] בכמ"ר מרדכי</name> היום יום ד ט"ו לחדש אדר ראשון שנת <date calendar="Hebrew">השמ"ב</date> ליצירה.<locus n="242r"/>
							</colophon>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Tikune_Zohar_1867"/>
								</bibl>
							</listBibl>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the second half of the 16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>242 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>320</height>
										<width>220</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>230</height>
										<width>125</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>242 folios (+ 1 unfoliated paper flyleaf at the beginning and 14 at the end). Folios 1-9 are paper flyleaves.</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 8 leaves each.</p>
									<p>Original Hebrew foliation, from folio 10 onwards, extends from no. 283 to 515 (continuing the foliation of Add MS 27060).</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Stained.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 2" ruledLines="40" writtenLines="40">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Visible hard-point ruling.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso.</p>
									<p>Initial words in larger square characters.</p>
									<p>Running titles.</p>
									<p>A number of marginal notes and comments.</p>
									<p>Folio 1-9 left blank.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Italian semi-cursive script (for the main text and for the commentary) of the second half of the 16th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Ya῾aḳov ben Mordekhai Pogeṭṭi</name>: inscribed in the colophon, folio 242r.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Boniforte del Asinary</name>: Italian censor (active 1575-1599 in Asti): inscribed with his name: 'Visto et coretto per me Boniforte del Asinary' (folio 242r); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="number">V</ref>.</p>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Hieronimus Carolus</name>: inscribed with his name: 'Inqu. Asti. Die 19 Febr. 1582'  (folio 242r).</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Post-1600. Dark red leather, blind tooled, with marks of clasps. Boxed.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Moses Cordovero. Or Yakar. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional 27,061.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
					</physDesc>
